{"type":"text","timestamp":1781762693265,"sessionID":"ses_126add179ffeFYyiaZOsieAbUe","part":{"id":"prt_ed95502fa001Ftf5GtTGg7Bs6X","messageID":"msg_ed954d95e001dqM6EwcitRzirn","sessionID":"ses_126add179ffeFYyiaZOsieAbUe","type":"text","text":"A stronger lifecycle candidate is soft-delete idempotency: the tombstone helpers update `updated_at` even if `deleted_at` is already set, so repeated delete calls may report new deletions and emit duplicate audit/ledger rows. I’m checking whether callers filter tombstoned rows before confirming.","time":{"start":1781762687738,"end":1781762693262},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_071c84d92e422b80016a338a7fb5648191b93e377611d8d882","phase":"commentary"}}}}
