mented.\n- Do not record repeated soft-delete response behavior as confirmed defect without stronger evidence because tests cover tombstone behavior.\n\n## Next Steps\n- Complete targeted review of SQL/path/cancellation/lifecycle evidence.\n- Write required deep-review artifacts under `.../lineages/gpt55r2-b-5`:\n  1. `deep-review-config.json`\n  2. `deep-review-state.jsonl`\n  3. `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n  4. `deep-review-strategy.md`\n  5. `deep-review-dashboard.md`\n  6. `iterations/iteration-001.md`\n  7. `review-report.md`\n- Run synthesis with stop reason `maxIterations`.\n- Output exactly `FANOUT_LINEAGE_COMPLETE:gpt55r2-b-5`.\n\n## Critical Context\n- Memory preflight error: `Error: sessionId \"fanout-gpt55r2-b-5-1781761339355-o7qylx\" does not match a server-managed session. Omit sessionId to start a new server-generated session and reuse the effectiveSessionId returned by the server.`\n- Retry without `session_id` returned: `No matching trigger phrases found`.\n- Code graph status: `freshness: stale`; reason: `git HEAD changed: 8b9ff540 -> 2b64f293; 442 stale files exceed selective threshold (50)`.\n- Review dimensions: correctness, security, data integrity, concurrency/cancellation, performance, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift.\n- Scope file says clean PASS is valid if no real P0/P1/P2 findings are found.\n\n## Relevant Files\n- `/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md`: workflow contract.\n- `/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`: artifact/verdict quick reference.\n- `/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`: lifecycle protocol.\n- `/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workfl